-- Eurotech, Cisco Sign Agreement Allowing Italian Company to Offer Products
-- B y   C h i a r a   R e m o n d i n i
-- 2010-12-13T09:01:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-13/eurotech-cisco-sign-agreement-allowing-italian-company-to-offer-products.html
Eurotech SpA, an Italian maker of
miniature and rugged computers, said it signed an accord with
Cisco Systems Inc. that will allow it to add products by the 
largest maker of networking equipment to its next-generation
solutions.  Under the agreement, Eurotech will create “competitive
solutions for the transportation market,” the Amaro, Italy-
based company said in a statement today. “As a member of the
Cisco Solution Technology Integrator program, we can offer
Eurotech customers a superior product,” it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chiara Remondini at 
 cremondini@bloomberg.net  